data.title: Handout - SurEngLit I - Part I
data.meta_description: Handout - SurEngLit I - Part I - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The document provides an overview of the key elements in the medieval poem Sir Gawain and the Green Knight including its structure, themes, and characters. It follows the journey of the knight Sir Gawain who accepts a challenge from the Green Knight to meet him in one year's time. Over the course of the poem, Gawain struggles with maintaining his chivalric virtues as he is tempted by the Lady of the castle. In the end, his failure to be completely honest results in a loss of confidence in himself and the society he represents.
